properties.title: São Bento Railway Station
properties.description: São Bento Railway Station is located in the city of Porto, in Portugal. The station was inaugurated in 1916, and it is known for its floor-to-ceiling azulejo tile work that illustrates Portugal's history and rulers, as well as the progress of means of transport, up to the early 1900s. There are a whopping 20,000 tiles in total in this light-filled station.

properties.title: Port of Leixões
properties.description: The Port of Leixões was built in the end of the 19th century and it has been successively extended and improved to the present day. It is one of Portugal's major seaports, with the largest port infrastructure in the Northern Region in the country. It is located 4 km north of the mouth of the Douro River, in the municipality of Matosinhos, in the Greater Porto area.

properties.title: Campanhã Intermodal Transport Terminal
properties.description: Porto Customs House Congress Centre sits next to the river Douro and the historical centre. The building’s unique dimension and architecture, designed by Eduardo Souto de Moura, are attributes that make this the ideal venue for corporative, scientific, cultural and commercial events.
